description: Pyannote/speaker-diarization-3.1 is an open-source toolkit written in Python for speaker diarization, which is the task of determining "who spoke when" in an audio recording. It is based on the PyTorch machine learning framework and provides a set of trainable end-to-end neural building blocks that can be combined and jointly optimized.
